  "After years of advocacy, a community successfully gets a polluting factory shut down and the site cleaned up. Federal investments then bring a new transit station, bike lanes, and organic grocery store. However, property taxes double, rents triple, and most original residents are forced to move to another polluted neighborhood across town. What does this cycle reveal about the limitations of current environmental justice approaches?": "",
